// techdesign-splices-desugars-sonnet.md §2.2/§2.3(3): `on class C` stays
// exact — it does NOT fire on a struct (no `on type`/`on struct` twin here,
// unlike rule_subject_type.ext) — and the misleading "missing uses" warning
// is replaced by a kind-aware note pointing at 'on type' / 'on struct'.
// @no-roundtrip: the warning is a property of the ORIGINAL source's rule
// declaration, which --expand does not print back (rule decls are
// compile-time-only, gone from the expanded artifact) — the round-tripped
// file has no rule left to mismatch against, so the warning doesn't re-fire.
namespace Marker {
    attribute Serializable { }
    rule tagClass {
        match @Serializable(x) on class C
        inject `int kindTag() => 1;` at member of C
    }
}
uses Marker;

class Widget { }

@Serializable
struct Point { int x; int y; }

console.writeln(9);
